1. DEFINITIONS
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

   "Software" means the source code, compiled artefacts, configuration,
   prompts, prompt templates, system designs, documentation,
   architecture diagrams, database schemas, and all other content in
   this repository, plus any future updates, modifications, or
   derivative works thereof. The Software is a "computer programme"
   and a "literary work" within the meaning of Section 2(o) and
   Section 2(ffc) of the Copyright Act, 1957.

   "Owner" means Aarohan Verma, an Indian national and the sole
   author and first owner of the copyright in the Software within the
   meaning of Section 17 of the Copyright Act, 1957.

   "Permission" means a written grant from the Owner — by email
   from verma.aarohan@gmail.com or by a signed document (including
   an electronic record signed with a digital or electronic signature
   under the Information Technology Act, 2000) — explicitly authorising
   a named party to perform a specific act with respect to the
   Software.

   "Use" means any of the following acts performed by any person or
   entity, in whole or in part, in any environment: executing;
   running; deploying; hosting; serving; making available over a
   network; embedding; bundling; integrating into another product;
   training, fine-tuning, or evaluating any machine-learning model
   on; or otherwise putting the Software into operational service.

   "Derivative" means any fork, clone, modification, adaptation, port,
   translation, extension, plug-in, or other work based on the
   Software in whole or in part, and includes any "adaptation" within
   the meaning of Section 2(a) of the Copyright Act, 1957.

   "Attribution" means the visible credit specified in Section 5.

