13. DISPUTE RESOLUTION — ARBITRATION
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

   (a) Any dispute, controversy, difference, or claim arising out of
       or in connection with this licence, including any question
       regarding its existence, validity, breach, termination, or the
       infringement of any intellectual property right relating to
       the Software, shall be referred to and finally resolved by
       arbitration under the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996,
       as amended from time to time.

   (b) The arbitration shall be conducted by a sole arbitrator.
       Failing agreement between the parties on the identity of the
       sole arbitrator within thirty (30) days of a written request
       to arbitrate, the arbitrator shall be appointed in accordance
       with Section 11 of the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996.

   (c) The seat and venue of arbitration shall be Bengaluru,
       Karnataka, India.

   (d) The language of the arbitration shall be English.

   (e) The arbitral award shall be final and binding on the parties
       and shall be enforceable in any court of competent
       jurisdiction.

   (f) Notwithstanding the foregoing, the Owner shall be entitled at
       any time, and without prejudice to the arbitration agreement,
       to seek interim, urgent, or injunctive relief — including ex
       parte and John Doe orders — from any court of competent
       jurisdiction under Section 9 of the Arbitration and
       Conciliation Act, 1996, or otherwise, to restrain or remedy
       any actual or threatened infringement of the Owner's rights
       in the Software.

